      "text": "WHY MICHIGAN #1 IN COMPOSITE (despite Duke's highest KADJ EM)\n\n                   KADJ EM   BADJ EM   Neutral   RADJ EM   RelRtg    KADJ D    EXP\n  Michigan (1)      37.59     36.59     38.10     38.30     34.50     89.03    1.95\n  Arizona  (1)      37.66     35.53     38.40     38.60     32.05     90.02    1.41\n  Duke     (1)      38.90     37.32     32.90     39.90     34.83     89.06    0.86\n\n  Duke leads raw KADJ EM but DROPS 6 pts on neutral courts (32.9 vs 38.1 Michigan)\n  Michigan: best EXP (1.95 veterans), best Killshots (+1.00), #1 Injury Rank\n  Arizona: best neutral-court BADJ EM (38.4), best pure defense (KADJ D 90.0)\n  Duke EXP 0.86 = youngest team in tourney -- historically a March liability\n  Composite weights neutral performance (20%) and experience (2.5%) --> Michigan edges Duke",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": "r_67",
      "originalText": "WHY MICHIGAN #1 IN COMPOSITE (despite Duke's highest KADJ EM)\n\n                   KADJ EM   BADJ EM   Neutral   RADJ EM   RelRtg    KADJ D    EXP\n  Michigan (1)      37.59     36.59     38.10     38.30     34.50     89.03    1.95\n  Arizona  (1)      37.66     35.53     38.40     38.60     32.05     90.02    1.41\n  Duke     (1)      38.90     37.32     32.90     39.90     34.83     89.06    0.86\n\n  Duke leads raw KADJ EM but DROPS 6 pts on neutral courts (32.9 vs 38.1 Michigan)\n  Michigan: best EXP (1.95 veterans), best Killshots (+1.00), #1 Injury Rank\n  Arizona: best neutral-court BADJ EM (38.4), best pure defense (KADJ D 90.0)\n  Duke EXP 0.86 = youngest team in tourney -- historically a March liability\n  Composite weights neutral performance (20%) and experience (2.5%) --> Michigan edges Duke",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
